SIMPLE: forget
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forget
<hw>For*get"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Forgot</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>
(<conjf>Forgat</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <mark>Obs</mark>.); <pos>p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Forgotten</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>, <conjf>Forgot</conjf>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Forgetting</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[OE. <ets>forgeten</ets>, <ets>foryeten</ets>, AS.
<ets>forgietan</ets>, <ets>forgitan</ets>; pref. <ets>for-</ets> +
<ets>gietan</ets>, <ets>gitan</ets> (only in comp.), to get; cf. D.
<ets>vergeten</ets>, G. <ets>vergessen</ets>, Sw.
<ets>f⟦oum⟧rg⟦aum⟧ta</ets>, Dan. <ets>forgiette</ets>. See
<er>For-</er>, and <er>Get</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To lose the remembrance of; to let go from the memory; to cease to
have in mind; not to think of; also, to lose the power of; to cease from
doing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Bless the Lord, O my soul, and <qex>forget</qex> not all his
benefits.</q> <rj><qau>Ps. ciii. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let my right hand <qex>forget</qex> her cunning.</q> <rj><qau>Ps.
cxxxvii. 5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hath thy knee <qex>forget</qex> to bow?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To treat with inattention or disregard; to slight;
to neglect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Can a woman <qex>forget</qex> her sucking child? . . . Yes, they
may <qex>forget</qex>, yet will I not <qex>forget</qex> thee.</q>
<rj><qau>Is. xlix. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To forget one's self</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>To
become unmindful of one's own personality; to be lost in thought.</cd>
<sd>(b)</sd> <cd>To be entirely unselfish.</cd> <sd>(c)</sd> <cd>To be
guilty of what is unworthy of one; to lose one's dignity, temper, or
self-control.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forgetful</ent>⟦br⟧
